sentences: Dan Willson (born 23 July 1974), also known by his stage name Withered Hand, is an Edinburgh-based indie rock musician.
He lived in Bishops Stortford during the 1990s and played guitar for local band Tin Foil Circus.
His first studio album, Good News, was released in 2009 in Scotland, and re-released in 2011 on Absolutely Kosher Records in the United States.
His first studio album, Good News, was released in 2009 in Scotland, and re-released in 2011 on Absolutely Kosher Records in the United States.
His second album, entitled New Gods, was released in March 2014 through Fortuna Pop Records in the UK and Slumberland Records in the USA.
He performed at the South by Southwest festival in Austin, Texas in 2011 and 2014, as part of the Scottish Showcase.
He has been based in Edinburgh since 1996.
Willson studied at Art College in London, and moved to Edinburgh with his then-girlfriend, to whom he is now married, in 1996.
He was guitarist in Edinburgh band Barrichello, which he joined in 1999.
This band broke up amicably in 2002.
Robert Christgau has also written favorable reviews of both his albums, naming Good News the 14th best album of 2011  and New Gods the 3rd best album of 2014.
